Palindrome (marco@suncis.epm.br) wrote:
: 	Hello, I am wondering where I could find a good random character generator. Security is a concern, speed is NOT.

   Obtain two dice of different colors. Make a chart 6 rows by 6 columns. 
fill the spaces with a-z, 0-9. Label the left side one color, top side 
the other.
   Every roll of these two dice gives one character in the range a-z,0-9. 
This gives 5.17 bits of security per character. If you need 50 bits roll 
10 times.
-Steve

